I can tell right now that you like spells...so even though I'm a melee-guy, I'm going to say you might as well forget the Warrior and the Rogue.  Not only that, but you mention solo'ing quite a bit, so that's another reason to forget them.

Now, Clerics have tough solo'ing as well...and you're right, they are repetitive.  Keep this one around, but probably not as a main or secondary main.

That leaves Ranger and Mage.  Hybrid and Int Caster.  Not a bad couple of classes, either.

Both of them can solo, albeit the Ranger might have a bit tougher of a time due to being limited to soloing animals only (more on this, however).

Mages - well, I hate playing INT classes.  But that's just me.  They are awesome classes, don't get me wrong, I just can't stand them for me playing them.  Others, with me in a group, are fun as hell...and very important, too.

Your mage is already 29, so you've already dealth with the biggest problem of Int Casters - research.  You don't get all your spells w/o doing research.  It's a PITA (Pain In The Ass).

But, the fact that you're 29 screams to me to keep it. (Another reason I said to keep the cleric...5 more levels to CH, and you can get in almost any group).

I recommend soloing your Mage in Echo Caverns, on Needlites.  Put a DS (Damage Shield) on your pet (my mage newbness is showing - isn't the fire pet auto ds?) and kill needlites until 32/33.  Then head to DSP (Dawnshroud Peaks).

Take your ranger and solo/group in PC.  Everyone can solo to 22-25, though once you hit your low 20s, the bandit camp groups are best.  DPS and Snare are lovely for them, so Rangers should be taken in quickly if spots are open.  If not, then solo the shrooms.

Once mid 20s, take your Ranger to Needlites and use those awesome DS spells, snare, and your DPS to wipe them out to low 30s.  Then go to DSP and, using animal fear spells, solo the Zelniaks to your heart's content (ie around level 40).


[edit: when I say drop your warrior and rogue, I do NOT mean delete them.  You never know when you might want to play them again.  I made my ranger in Feb 2001.  She didn't get played, pretty much at all, during the whole of 2002 or was it 2003?  Almost a year of not even being logged in.  She was in her mid 20s or so.  Now, she is 36 and flying through her levels.]

